description.plain:
Kyle Thomas Harvey (born May 18, 1993), known by his stage names KYLE and SuperDuperKyle and previously known as “K.i.D,” is a rapper and singer, songwriter, and actor from Ventura, California. His fan base grew through social media sites such as Facebook and YouTube–a fact he references in his song “Doubt It.”

Kyle has released two mixtapes–2013’s Beautiful Loser and his sophomore effort, 2015’s Smyle. In addition, he released many mixtapes while he was in high school under the name K.i.D, which helped him to hone his skills.

He was named to the 2017 XXL Freshman Class, along with XXXTENTACION, A Boogie Wit Da Hoodie, and more.

On May 18th of 2018 KYLE released his debut album Light Of Mine which further expanded on his style and ability to sing and rap.

He’s often compared to his influences, such as Drake and Kid Cudi. He gained popularity from collaborations with artists like Chance The Rapper and G-Eazy and rose to fame with his first top 10 single “iSpy” featuring Lil Yachty. He is currently signed to Atlantic Records.

description.plain:
KYLE and Lil Yachty link up for “iSpy,” a song about spotting cuties online.

The song was originally hinted at by KYLE on Twitter:

https://twitter.com/SuperDuperKyle/status/804500306746716160

As a single, it peaked at #4 on the Billboard Hot 100 and charted in fifteen countries total.

Eventually, it was featured as the ultimate track on Kyle’s major label debut album, Light of Mine.

songs.title: Playinwitme

description.plain:
“Playinwitme” is the second 2018 release from KYLE, coming 11 days after “To The Moon.”

KYLE and Oakland artist Kehlani sing about a female significant other that is in and out of their life and wasting precious time by playing games.

The song was premiered on Zane Lowe’s Beats 1 Radio show.
